{"type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Bases-First (Recommended)\n      Each issue is a note. Bases provide the views.\n      Issues are plain Markdown files with frontmatter properties (status, priority, project, due date, parent). Obsidian Bases (`.base` files) query these notes and display them as tables, grouped by status or project. No community plugins needed.\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Built entirely on core Obsidian features (Bases, properties, wikilinks)\n            Each issue is a full note — rich descriptions, links to docs vaults, sub-tasks via wikilinks\n            Bases give you table/list/card views with filters, grouping, and formulas out of the box\n            Easy to extend — add a new property and it just works\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            No true kanban board view (Bases doesn't have a board/column layout)\n            Many files over time — need good folder structure and archive strategy","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1773195886653}
